Player

“That is discouraging. We've done the best we could thus far.”

Player

Player

“The Business Council is satisfied with this infrastructure improvement.”

Player

“Focusing on future investments is better as more opportunities are surely on the horizon.”

Player

“Good. Just as expected.”

Player

“Excellent news. I hope to hear more of it.”

“It isn't good for our reputation. The people expected quick solutions. We are running out of time.”

The team gathered in Holsord at the Ministry of Economy to go over the current economic situation.

Mikail Aven

“Thanks to the highway, economic growth is returning to Agnland. We are expecting new investments and jobs in the region.”

Mikail Aven

“Thanks to the high-speed railway our two most important cities are linked faster. We are expecting quick economic growth in Greater Holsord and Gelsland.”

Gus Manger

“Let's make sure that it won't be unfair.”

Gus Manger

“If the budget allows it.”

Edith Agnoc

“Agreed. Any reliance on credit could endanger our future.”

Edith Agnoc

“We need to fix the issues... Not punish people.”

The building was constructed in 1892 by Heron Walt, possibly the most famous architect in Sordland. It was a simple and elegant structure with a few of his signature domes spread out over the roof.

Gus Manger

“I actually agree with you. Lileas had a very prominent role.”

Symon Holl

“Good to hear. We will do better.”

Deivid Wisci

“I am not so sure about that. But time will tell. I still see it as risky. Our support for their military operation was questionable.”

Edith Agnoc

“On a side note, consumer spending has increased due to the optimistic mood caused by our economic successes.”

Edith Agnoc

“I support our foreign initiatives with partners as democratic as Agnolia.”

Edith Agnoc

“I must say, I still can't get behind a trade deal with Wehlen, especially when it involved a military cooperation.”

Symon Holl

“Increased trade has improved our economy. I see this as a reason for celebration.”

Symon Holl

“Good to hear. We will do better.”

Gus Manger

“The people are already speaking of the positive turn.”

Player

“Your efforts are noted. Everyone who has contributed is greatly appreciated.”

Gus Manger

“Teamwork makes the dream work.”

Player

“We should look for more trade partners. We can make much more and increase our presence in the region.”

Deivid Wisci

“I agree. Not just the region -- we should aim for more deals internationally.”

Player

“That's beside the point.”

Narrator

Edith didn't reply, but she smiled.

Deivid Wisci

“Our trade deal with Wehlen has increased our imports and exports by 60% in one month, which is a considerably good number.”

Player

“It was a good idea to align with Wehlen.”

Player

“Perfect.”

“I feel like we have made a contract with the devil.”

Player

“I didn't ask you for your opinion.”

Player

“We are reaping the benefits. We will come out on top here.”

Deivid Wisci

“Albeit risky, it is lucrative.”

Deivid Wisci

“I am not only worried about Wehlen. It's the other countries too.”

Symon Holl

“Deivid, do you have the stats on our deal with Agnolia?”

Deivid Wisci

“We are sorry, Mr. President.”

Player

“The responsibility falls on me.”

Player

“We don't need other countries. Sordland is enough for itself.”

Deivid Wisci

“Our trade with other countries increased slightly below our expected growth rate due to the failed negotiations.”

Deivid Wisci

“Don't blame yourself.”

Symon Holl

“Some good news. We currently have a budget surplus.”

Symon Holl

“Unless anything changes ,of course.”

Symon Holl

“I'm afraid it's still a bit too early for a celebration.”

Symon Holl

“Thank you, Mr. President.”

Symon Holl

“Exactly, but no use worrying.”

Symon Holl

“If we are unable to stop this recession, we are heading towards an economic catastrophe that has never been seen before in Sordland.”

Symon Holl

“I can't even begin to imagine how we could survive that. None of us wants to see Sordish people starve while the state is unable to provide for its citizens.”

Player

“Then we need to get to work.”

Symon Holl

“Our surplus is a great reason to spend extra on a new investment project to push for further economic development in the future.”

Symon Holl

“There are two main distinctions between these projects. It's either about continuing our infrastructure improvements or investing in increasing production.”

Symon Holl

“I have prepared a few project proposals.”

Symon Holl

“The plans for these projects will be finalized soon. For now, I can provide preliminary information. Which one would you like to hear first?”

Player

“I have enough information.”

Player

“Economic growth in Benfi could be propelled. It still has yet to reach its full potential.”

Mikail Aven

“Benfi is growing at a rapid pace and would benefit highly from a international airport. Much more money to be made there too.”

Deivid Wisci

“I agree with Edith. The Morna port will mean a great deal to our trade and improve the economy of the Lorren region too.”

Player

“What are the projects that could boost our production?”

Edith Agnoc

“The recession has hit the farmers of Sarna particularly hard. Besides the agricultural output increase would boost our economy.”

Symon Holl

“For production we have two projects. One is the Sarna Agricultural Zone and the other is the Conriat Industrial City.”

Mikail Aven

“We should invest and develop Conriat to diversify the economy in Greater Holsord which would mean a great deal.”

Deivid Wisci

“I see the Sarna Agricultural Zone investment as a higher priority due to the fact that farmers in Bergia were the most hit by the recession. Sarna also is a much poorer city than Conriat.”

Edith Agnoc

“There is of course the option to not take any risks related to our budget.”

Symon Holl

“Very well.”

Player

“Edith, how strong is our currency?”

Player

“Mikail, how is the mood at the National Business Council?”

Player

“Anybody who wants to add something?”

Narrator

Nobody answered.

Symon Holl

“That concludes the meeting. Have a good day, all.”

Edith Agnoc

“Currency health has greatly improved thanks to the strong economic action of the administration and the value of the Ren has also increased beyond expectations.”

Deivid Wisci

“We have imported and exported more across the board with all countries except, Rumburg.”

Questions Hub

Player

“I have a couple more economy related questions.”

Mikail Aven

“They are holding on to their investments until they feel it is safe to invest their reserves in new hires or branches.”

Narrator

The meeting ended.

Gus Manger

“See you soon.”

Mikail Aven

“The business leaders in the council are nervous about the lack of tangible economic improvements in the country.”

Deivid Wisci

“Our inability to reach a trade deal has hurt our position as a regional trade partner countries were looking to.”

Deivid Wisci

“Until next time, Mr. President.”

Edith Agnoc

“Goodbye.”

“Currency health and economic output improved the Sordish Ren post-elections but due to the recent developments our currency value decreased.”

Edith Agnoc

“There are observable losses at the Central Bank. When we compare pre-election levels, we see that inflation has increased by ten percentage points.”

Symon Holl

“Let's hear the stats on our deal with Wehlen.”

Player

“The devil? Wiktor Smolak is not a bad man.”

Deivid Wisci

“Our trade deal with Agnolia has increased our imports and exports by 25% in one month with much more to be expected in the future.”

Deivid Wisci

“But higher prices of Agnolian steel didn't result in a trade surplus.”

Player

“That's what we expected.”

Deivid Wisci

“That's true. Regardless of the surplus, Agnolia is an important partner to have.”

Symon Holl

“Let's begin without any further ado.”

Symon Holl

“The ongoing trade war between Arcasia and United Contana has disrupted global trade immensely.”

Symon Holl

“Our net losses are growing as a fallout, and we have lost a substantial amount of budget.”

Symon Holl

“Deivid?”

Player

“Good news for us. It will give us an edge over them.”

Deivid Wisci

“There is always a silver lining.”

Symon Holl

“We are doing everything we can to mitigate the disaster. The end of the tunnel is in sight, Mr. President.”

Gus Manger

“How are we doing in terms of our infrastructure?”

Gus Manger

“How are we doing in terms of our trade?”

Symon Holl

“It will be costly to get back on our feet, Mr. President. I don't know how to say this, but...”

Symon Holl

“Whatever we do, we need more budget. That's the bottom line. We need to squeeze out every single Sordish Ren we can to survive this.”

Symon Holl

“Like dominoes, of course, this will also affect the election.”

Player

“You are exaggerating. We will overcome this regardless. We survived so far.”

Player

“I will do whatever I can to bring us that budget. Even if that's the last thing I do.”

Symon Holl

“Otherwise... our country might be in a state to declare bankruptcy.”

Symon Holl

“Yes, and we need to fix this situation in order to do that.”

Symon Holl

“The aid we have received from Arcasia has helped us tremendously.”

Player

“Let's hope this decision won't come back to haunt us later on.”

Player

“I would expect nothing less from our United Contanan friends.”

Symon Holl

“Regardless of what they think, the capital will certainly be handy.”

Player

“Let's hope this decision won't come back to haunt us later on.”

Symon Holl

“There were many people who opposed this decision. Especially in the Lotherberg Group.”

Symon Holl

“We now have another weapon to combat the recession.”

Symon Holl

“I don't think that will be the case. Arcasians are known for their fair business.”

Symon Holl

“I don't think anyone in the room is questioning your decision, Mr. President.”

Symon Holl

“Well said!”

Symon Holl

“I sure do hope so as well.”

Symon Holl

“Sometimes we need to make sacrifices. I think everyone in this room understands that, Mr. President.”

Symon Holl

“If you say so, Mr. President.”

Symon Holl

“The good news is that the government has a perfectly balanced budget.”

Symon Holl

“We have the potential to take on additional debt to maintain the upward trend of the economy.”

Symon Holl

“If we stabilize our crumbling infrastructure it would support some growth later. However, our industrial production also needs a boost to return to pre-recession levels.”

Symon Holl

“There are two main distinctions between these projects. It's either we improve our poor infrastructure or we invest in increasing production.”

Edith Agnoc

"Currency health and economic output degraded significantly and nearly crashed the Sordish Ren. Our currency is on the course to actually crash if we don't act."

Symon Holl

“We have enough of a budget to survive this crisis for some time. In order to navigate the financial repercussions of Black Tuesday, we must act in a fiscally liberal manner.”

Edith Agnoc

“Furthermore, the recent 'Black Tuesday' event caused dramatic economic upheavals in Sordland and the wider region.”

Mikail Aven

“The NBC will also lend support to the analysis and contingency plans regarding the ongoing developments.”

Edith Agnoc

“The issues surrounding the energy prices and the imbalance they cause in the market are also of pressing concern. Average citizens and businesses are suffering.”

Edith Agnoc

“After the Central Bank Reinforcement Act, our focus will shift to primarily tackle the energy inflation crisis in the country. We will present a bill about this in the near future if the situation regresses.”

Edith Agnoc

“We are tackling these with measures we have in our power at the C.B. to stabilize the market.”

Symon Holl

“Our treasury is in a dangerous amount of debt.”

Symon Holl

“If we don't reduce our debt in the future we might fall in a debt crisis or worse.”

“What are you suggestions on tackling this?”

Player

“Maybe we should be more cautious with the treasury.”
